<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Zip on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/zip/</link><description>Recent content in Zip on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/zip/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Git Archive Creation Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/git/git-archive-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/git/git-archive-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A Git archive error occurs when &lt;code&gt;git archive&lt;/code&gt; fails to create a snapshot of the repository. This command exports the contents of a tree without the &lt;code&gt;.git&lt;/code&gt; directory, but can fail due to missing refs, invalid format options, or file system issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The specified branch, tag, or commit does not exist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Invalid output format specified&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Output file path is not writable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Disk space is insufficient&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The archive format does not match the output file extension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="verify-the-ref-exists"&gt;Verify the Ref Exists&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git log --oneline -1 main
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git tag -l
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="create-a-tar-archive"&gt;Create a Tar Archive&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git archive --format&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;tar HEAD -o snapshot.tar
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="create-a-zip-archive"&gt;Create a Zip Archive&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git archive --format&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;zip HEAD -o snapshot.zip
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="archive-a-specific-branch-or-tag"&gt;Archive a Specific Branch or Tag&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git archive --format&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;zip v1.0.0 -o release-v1.0.0.zip
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="archive-a-subdirectory"&gt;Archive a Subdirectory&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git archive --format&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;zip HEAD src/ -o src-only.zip
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-disk-space"&gt;Check Disk Space&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;df -h
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 1: Archive current branch&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git archive HEAD -o project.tar.gz
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 2: Archive a tag&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git archive v2.1.0 --format&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;zip -o v2.1.0.zip
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 3: Archive with prefix&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git archive --prefix&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;myproject-v1/ HEAD -o project.tar
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;tar -tf project.tar
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# myproject-v1/src/main.js&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# myproject-v1/README.md&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 4: List available formats&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git archive --list
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# tar&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# zip&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/git/git-fetch-error/"&gt;Git Fetch Error&lt;/a&gt; — fetch failed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/git/git-tag-error/"&gt;Git Tag Error&lt;/a&gt; — tag creation error&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/git/git-branch-error/"&gt;Git Branch Error&lt;/a&gt; — branch operation error&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python TypeError — zip_longest Issues</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/zip-longest/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/zip-longest/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="typeerror--zip_longest-issues"&gt;TypeError — zip_longest Issues&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;TypeError&lt;/code&gt; related to &lt;code&gt;itertools.zip_longest&lt;/code&gt; is raised when you call it incorrectly, such as passing non-iterable arguments, using wrong keyword arguments, or misunderstanding its behavior. &lt;code&gt;zip_longest&lt;/code&gt; is used to iterate over multiple iterables until the longest one is exhausted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;itertools.zip_longest&lt;/code&gt; takes multiple iterables and an optional &lt;code&gt;fillvalue&lt;/code&gt; keyword argument. It continues until the longest iterable is exhausted, filling missing values with &lt;code&gt;fillvalue&lt;/code&gt;. Errors occur when you pass non-iterables, use incorrect keyword arguments, or confuse it with &lt;code&gt;zip()&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>